<subSubSection id="5A9465406E4D3F0F4044FC71FB939347" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="123136CB6E4D3F0F4044FC71FB939347" blockId="25.[270,1103,919,1260]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E4D3F0F4044FC71FE0194FC" bold="true" box="[296,410,919,940]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head, posteriorly, of female rounded (
<figureCitation id="8AB52A4E6E4D3F0F422DFC71FC1194FC" box="[833,906,919,940]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[293,327,1246,1265]" captionTargetBox="[275,1100,238,1222]" captionTargetId="figure-12@11.[269,1104,234,1226]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Head (dorsal aspects of postcranium) of Agra species. a) varzeicola male; b) A. servatorum male; c) A. servatorum female; d) A. conhormigas male; e) A. lilu female; f) A. lindae male; g) A. rondonia male; h) A. nex female; i) A. manu female; j) A. dax male; k) A. dax female, l) A. sasquatch female." pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Fig. 3l</figureCitation>
), somewhat swollen. Ultimate labial palpomere (as in 
<figureCitation id="8AB52A4E6E4D3F0F43CBFC57FD679496" box="[679,764,945,966]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[293,327,1246,1265]" captionTargetBox="[275,1100,238,1222]" captionTargetId="figure-12@11.[269,1104,234,1226]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Head (dorsal aspects of postcranium) of Agra species. a) varzeicola male; b) A. servatorum male; c) A. servatorum female; d) A. conhormigas male; e) A. lilu female; f) A. lindae male; g) A. rondonia male; h) A. nex female; i) A. manu female; j) A. dax male; k) A. dax female, l) A. sasquatch female." pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E4D3F0F43CBFC57FD679496" bold="true" box="[679,764,945,966]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Fig. 3C</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) paralleliform, sides barely divergent, length greater than that of scape, narrower than in male. Tarsomeres without modified white setae. Elytral (
<figureCitation id="8AB52A4E6E4D3F0F43CCFC01FD7E94AC" box="[672,741,999,1020]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[293,327,1302,1321]" captionTargetBox="[289,1083,240,1277]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[282,1090,234,1282]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Elytron (left side, dorsal aspect of apex) of Agra species. a) A. tingo female; b) A. servatorum male; c) A. servatorum female; d) A. conhormigas male; e) A. lilu female; f) A. lindae male; g) A. rondonia male; h) A. nex female; i) A. manu female; j) A. dax male; k) A. dax female; l) A. sasquatch female." pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Fig. 6l</figureCitation>
) apex more elongate than in male. Venter without central pubescence of male. Female styli (as in 
<figureCitation id="8AB52A4E6E4D3F0F42DBFBE7FC639346" box="[951,1016,1025,1046]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[291,325,1313,1332]" captionTargetBox="[274,1096,237,1289]" captionTargetId="figure-12@16.[267,1102,234,1293]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 7. Aedeagus (dorsal/ventral/left lateral aspects) of Agra species. a) A. biolat; b) A. aeris; c) A. solimoes." pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E4D3F0F42DBFBE7FC639346" bold="true" box="[951,1016,1025,1046]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Fig. 7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
